                type="document" xml:id="d253">
                <head>253. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Harold Macmillan</persName> visited
                    Athens August 7–9 for talks with <persName corresp="#p_KC1"
                        >Karamanlis</persName> and Averoff on the future of Cyprus. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MH1">Macmillan</persName> then flew to Ankara where he met with
                        <persName corresp="#p_MA1">Menderes</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZFR1">Zorlu</persName> on August 9 and 10 for further
                    discussions on Cyprus. On August 11, <persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        >Macmillan</persName> flew to Cyprus to meet with British administrators and
                    representatives of the Greek and Turkish communities. For the Prime Minister’s
                    account of these meetings, see Riding the Storm, pages 674–683.</p>
            </div>
